In a press conference at the U.S. Capitol, President Biden expressed uncertainty about whether he can get the desired legislation passed. When asked about his confidence in getting the votes needed, he responded that he hopes it can be done, but he doesn't know for sure. He mentioned that if they miss the opportunity this time, they can try again in the future. The President also emphasized that the issue goes beyond voting rights and is about who gets to count the votes, highlighting concerns about election subversion. Despite the uncertainty, he vowed to continue fighting for changes in state legislatures.